**2020-11-09 TEAS**

ACTN can support multiple options at the MPI: it is possible to use only PCEP, as defined in RFC8637, or only the YANG models, as described in this document, or any possible combinations of PCEP and YANG models.

The scope of the text is just to clarify that all these possibilities exist.

@sergiobelotti : please check if this example is reported in some public document

For example, it is possible to use PCEP just for path computation and YANG models for the rest  (for example when PCEP has been already implemented/deployed).

@dancecca : are you ok to just add an example? Otherwise, what about the proposal in https://github.com/FabioPeruzzini/actn-poi/pull/30#issuecomment-723932249 to address the pros&cons description?

